Name: Student Solutions Manual for Fundamentals of Physics, Tenth Edition

ReviewList.Text: When you buy a solutions manual for a textbook it is expected that it will contain the solutions to chapter exercises.  This book, however, only contains a SMALL FRACTION of solutions... This is just a way for the publisher to suck another $70 out of you...as if the price of the actual textbook wasn't high enough already!  Don't bother...it's not worth the money.

Do not buy this solution manual. As the previous reviewer said, this book is very small and contain answers to VERY few questions. Usually, solution manual contain all the answers in details to odd-numbered questions. However, this book only answer few questions in detail. For example, chapter two in the textbook have +100 problem. This solution manual starts answering question 3, 5, than jumps to 19, than jumps to 23, jumps to 33, jumps to 45!!!
I ordered this for help on the chapter home work. It has been worth so little to me I regret not sending it back when I got it. So few questions are explained.
Useless. Does not have most of the answers. Not worth it. Missing so many problems, like 90% of the answers that are supposed to be there are missing.
Waste of time, money and hope. Most unhelpful book in history.
dont ever take a corse with wiley publishing or software its terrible!
